post_text:
The Glades County School District has been receiving questions, recently, concerning the state's Pandemic EBT Program. This program, sponsored by the Florida Department of Agriculture and the Florida Department of Children and Families, is a supplemental benefit for households with children who have temporarily lost access to free or reduced-price school meals due to pandemic-related school closures. The school district has contacted Tallahassee, and they let us know that everything is okay, and that eligible Glades County residents will be receiving their benefits. You can learn more about the program by visiting https://www.myflfamilies.com/covid19/access.shtml.

Thank you.

Congratulations! Glades School District is officially a Florida FAFSA Challenge Most Improved district for the 2019 – 2020 school year! This means that your district increased student completion rates of the Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) the most in the state by April 24th compared to March 29th of the 2018 – 2019 school year. We are pleased to recognize you as a Florida FAFSA Challenge Most Improved district!

Way to go students, parents, and administrators at MHMHS! We are so proud of your accomplishment!

post_text:
MHMHS Seniors:

Hope all of you are well. It has been our desire to honor you in the most profound way possible considering our restrictions and the unknown.

We want you to be able to celebrate your accomplishments and your future plans! You have worked so hard to get to this point, and we want you to be able to look back and have cherished memories of your graduation.

The original plan was set in motion with the idea of ensuring that all of you would be able to participate. However, we are not opposed to postponing if that is the consensus of your class.

With this in mind, you will be receiving a Graduation Plan survey today through your Google email. Please complete ASAP.

We are looking forward to hearing from all you!

Mrs. Jordan
Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
Dear Glades School Family,

Today, Governor Ron DeSantis and Commissioner of Education Richard Corcoran recommended that all Florida public and private K-12 schools continue distance learning and keep school campuses closed through June 3rd, the remainder of the 2019-2020 academic year.

Thank you for continuing to rally for your child’s education! I know that it has been a struggle, but you have all persevered! While this is is not the best scenario, we will all get through it together.

We will continue delivering meals and supporting your technology needs throughout the rest of this school year. More information will be forthcoming.

If you have any questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to reach out to your child’s administrators.

Thank you!
Kim Jordan
Superintendent of Schools

GCSD Families

I just wanted to reach out to all of you to say thank you!
Thank you for your encouragement. Thank you for your patience and understanding!
Thank you for your dedication to your children and their education.

These are trying times, but you have rose to the occasion in the most profound way!

Please check Facebook and Gladesedu.org for a link to our Glades e-Learning plan for families.
This is a guide to help you navigate your child’s education as we move forward. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to reach out to your child’s school.
Again thank you for your cooperation and determination to ensure your child continues learning in these unprecedented times.

Mrs. Jordan
Superintendent of Schools

Parents MUST come with their child to pick up a Chromebook. Please pull in to the south entrance at the front of the school (by the side parking lot) and make a single file line. Tuesday
Pre-K, Kindergarten and 1st Grade
3 to 6 pm

2nd and 3rd Grade
3 to 6 pm

3 to 6 pm

Report Cards will be given with Chromebooks and/or paper packets.

post_text:
As we continue our work to minimize the effects of the Coronavirus for all Glades County residents, the Glades County School District wishes to continue its commitment to ensuring that the youth of Glades County receive healthy meals. Beginning Monday, March 23, and continuing while the schools remain closed, the school district will deliver FREE bag breakfasts and lunches to our bus stops for all youth (ages 17 and under). We have created a schedule of delivery times, which is exactly four hours after our students’ normal pick up time. This can be viewed at our website, www.gladesedu.com. Students who wish to participate will receive one bag lunch and one bag breakfast at their bus stop when the school bus arrives. Please understand that the times will not be perfect at first-this is our first time trying this.

For walkers and car riders, we will also operate a ‘drive through’ service at the parent pick up behind Moore Haven Elementary School and the bus loop at West Glades School. Food will be distributed from 11:00 am until 11:30 am
Thank you.

post_text:
After careful deliberation, the school board selected Mrs. Kimberly Jordan to serve as the Interim Superintendent for the Glades County School Disrtict. Ms. Jordan was a former Teacher of the Year in Hendry County when she joined our district a few years ago to be the Assistant Principal of West Glades School. She transferred to the District Office in August to become the Director of Human Resources.
When an elected Superintendent resigns, he submits his resignation to the Governor of Florida. The Governor has the right to appoint a person of his choosing to serve as Interim Superintendent until the election in November. Ms. Jordan will serve as the Interim Superintendent until the Governor appoints a successor, or until the election, whichever happens sooner.
Congratulations, Mrs. Jordan! Thank you for agreeing to step up to help our children and our schools during this transition period!

WGS Celebrates Literacy

West Glades School participated in Celebrate Literacy Week during the week of January 27-31. Book Talks were viewed during morning announcements featuring some of our WGS students telling about their favorite books. On Thursday, students wore pajamas to "Snuggle Up with a Good Book" and all students were able to select a new book to take home. On Friday, students were able to dress as their favorite book character. A highlight of the week is the "friendly" competition between classes to be the first to identify the title of a book after hearing a short clue. Students then dash to the playground to be the first with the answer. Book clues are from the current FRA and Sunshine State lists. Thank you to all the WGS students and staff who did a great job celebrating literacy!

The Glades County School District is currently seeking bus drivers. Drivers work 4 hours/day, 186 days/year, with full benefits and a competitive hourly rate.
QUALIFICATIONS:
(1) High school diploma or equivalent.
(2) Valid Commercial Driver’s License (CDL), Class B, with airbrake, passenger (P) and school bus (S) endorsements.
(3) Valid certification in cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) and first aid.
(4) Must be physically capable of safely operating a motor vehicle and/or mechanized machinery in accordance with the job description.
(5) Satisfactory criminal background check and drug screening.
Please visit visit the School District Office at 400 10th Street Moore Haven, FL, or click on 'Employment Opportunities' on our website and scroll down to 'Non-Instructional Application", to apply.

(4) Must be physically capable of safely operating a motor vehicle and/or mechanized machinery in accordance with the job description.
(5) Satisfactory criminal background check and drug screening.
Please visit visit the School District Office at 400 10th Street Moore Haven, FL, or click on 'Employment Opportunities' on our website and scroll down to 'Non-Instructional Application", to apply.

post_text:
WGS Pollinator Presentation

Ms. Noreen Berden and Ms. Katlyn Woodruff from the Hendry and Glades Soil & Water Conservation Districts were recent visitors at West Glades School. Students in Mrs. Huysman's library classes had a lesson about honeybees and were able to have a presentation from these ladies about pollination. Information was also given about the poster contest "Where would we BEE without Pollinators". All students wishing to participate in the poster contest will be provided with posterboard from their office. Additionally, WGS has been provided with a Book Barn that is on loan during the duration of this project. It features many resource books that can be used as students research pollination. At the end of the presentation, all students were provided with honey stix in order to sample the delicious treat. Students and teachers would like to extend their thanks to Ms. Berden and Ms. Woodruff for this educational event.

Our 3rd Grade students and teachers participated in America Recycles Day by completing a service learning project called Playground Cleanup! Students went around MHES grounds and collected as much trash as they could find. Students were able to collect 29 pounds of trash! They learned all about the effects of plastic pollution on our environment.

Third Grade would love to challenge other grades to participate over the next few months and see if they can collect more trash than them!
